		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Tried my new PowerPak today on my PAL NES but with wierd results. Check out my mpeg-file I captured here:
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.anes.se/powerpak.mpg">http://www.anes.se/powerpak.mpg</a><!-- m -->
<br />Image quality is poor but I'll guess you'll see the wierd stripes that appear. My connector in my NES is new!
<br />
<br />The same PowerPak works very good on my Famicom A/V, these bugs aren't there..
<br />
<br />Hints what's wrong?
<br />
<br />EDIT: Discovered the demo, "quantum_disco_brothers_by_wAMMA.nes" looks terrible aswell, BUT, when the logo comes up after a short while, *pow* the distorsions disappear! Have tried many (PAL) games but they all have distorsions..
<br />
<br />EDIT2: Me and my friends old "intro" <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://patpend.net/ftp/roms/nes/fade2black.lha">http://patpend.net/ftp/roms/nes/fade2black.lha</a><!-- m --> works without glitches (no distorsions at all!) Sounds like a powerpak software problem?

		

